               🌳Example with n = 32  n is size of array
               Levels of recursion:
               Level 0 → 32 elements
               Level 1 → 16 + 16
               Level 2 → 8 + 8 + 8 + 8
               Level 3 → 4 + 4 + 4 + 4 + 4 + 4 + 4 + 4
               Level 4 → 2 × 16 times
               Level 5 → 1 × 32 times

               🧠 Work done at each level

               At every level, you process ALL elements once during merging:

               Level 0 → 32
               Level 1 → 16+16 = 32
               Level 2 → 8+8+8+8 = 32
               Level 3 → 4×8 = 32
               Level 4 → 2×16 = 32
               Level 5 → 1×32 = 32

               👉 So:

               Work per level = n = 32

               For n = 32:
                tc  Total Work = Work per level × Number of levels
                               = n × log₂(n)
                               = 32 × log₂(32)
                               = 32 × 5
                               = 160  (exact work units)

               ⇒ O(n log n)


