Nice — now you’re thinking like someone who actually **understands patterns**, not just memorizing. Let’s do the *same style breakdown* for the 3 basic sorts:

* 🔼 Bubble Sort (max goes to end)
* 🔽 Selection Sort (min goes to start)
* ✍️ Insertion Sort

And we’ll use n = 32 just like your merge sort notes.




Your merge sort had:
_______________________________
|                             |
|  divide → levels → merge
|_____________________________|

But these sorts are not divide-and-conquer.

👉 Instead, they work like:
_______________
|              |
  Pass 1
  Pass 2
  Pass 3
    ...
  Pass (n-1)
|______________|

So instead of “levels”, think “passes”


🔼 1. Bubble Sort (Max goes to end)

💡 Idea:
_________________________________________________________
|                                                       |
| Each pass pushes the **largest element to the end
|_______________________________________________________|

🌳 Structure (n = 32)
_____________________________
|                           |
  Pass 1 → 31 comparisons
  Pass 2 → 30 comparisons
  Pass 3 → 29 comparisons

   Pass 31 → 1 comparison
|___________________________|

🔥 Total Work

= 31 + 30 + 29 + ... + 1
= n(n-1)/2
= 32×31/2
= 496


 ✅ Final


Total Work = 496
TC = O(n²)

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
🔽 2. Selection Sort (Min goes to start)

💡 Idea:

Each pass finds the **minimum** and places it at correct position

🌳 Structure (n = 32)
__________________________________________________
|                                                |
  Pass 1 → find min from 32 → 31 comparisons
  Pass 2 → find min from 31 → 30 comparisons
  Pass 3 → 29 comparisons
  ...
  Pass 31 → 1 comparison
  ```
|________________________________________________|

🔥 Total Work


= 31 + 30 + 29 + ... + 1
= 496


⚠️ Important difference

* Bubble → many swaps
* Selection → only **1 swap per pass**

 ✅ Final


Total Work = 496
TC = O(n²)


✍️ 3. Insertion Sort

💡 Idea:

Take element and insert it in correct position in sorted part

🌳 Structure (n = 32)

Worst case (reverse sorted):
_____________________________
|                            |
  Pass 1 → 1 comparison
  Pass 2 → 2 comparisons
  Pass 3 → 3 comparisons
  ...
  Pass 31 → 31 comparisons
  ```
|___________________________|

🔥 Total Work


= 1 + 2 + 3 + ... + 31
= 496
```


⚡ Best Case (IMPORTANT)

If already sorted:

Each pass → 1 comparison
Total = 31
TC = O(n)


 ✅ Final

Worst = 496 → O(n²)
Best = 32 → O(n)


# 🧩 FINAL COMPARISON (n = 32)

| Algorithm        | Work Done   | Time Complexity |
| ---------------- | ----------- | --------------- |
| Merge Sort       | ~160        | O(n log n)      |
| Bubble Sort      | 496         | O(n²)           |
| Selection Sort   | 496         | O(n²)           |
| Insertion Sort   | 496 (worst) | O(n²)           |
| Insertion (best) | 32          | O(n)            |

